<font color="#FF0000">THOUGHTS ON REMEMBRANCE</font><br>
<tt>Tue Apr 29  2:32:43 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Chet,<br>
     It sometimes feels strange how all our different tours have played out in time.  30 years ago, and 2 weeks before Memorial Day, I was 3 weeks from graduation and commissioning and getting a daisy stuck in my M1 at the Chancellor's Review. Active duty didn't come till November, and orders for Vietnam, not till the next Memorial Day. After participating in the ceremonies at Philly's Memorial, will join you from a distance in raising a glass.
<p><code>-- gerald_ney@icpphil.navy.com  (Gerald Ney, &quot;professor&quot;, 7/68-7/69) </code><p>


